8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 176, L.D. 273, “An Act to Preserve
10 Legislative Authority over Investigating Committees”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act Related to the Issuance of Subpoena Power to Entities Created by Executive
13 Order'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 3 MRSA c. 38 is enacted to read:
17 CHAPTER 38
18 SUBPOENA POWER GRANTED BY THE LEGISLATURE
19 §1011. Subpoena power granted to entities created by executive order
20 The Legislature may grant the authority to administer oaths, issue subpoenas and take
21 depositions to an entity created by executive order by an affirmative vote of 2/3 of the
22 members present in each House of the Legislature.'
23 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
24 number to read consecutively.
25 SUMMARY
2266 This amendment replaces the bill. It provides that the Legislature may grant the
2277 authority to administer oaths, issue subpoenas and take depositions to an entity created by
